President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Joseph P. Mohorovic for the position of Commissioner at the Consumer Product Safety Commission. Mohorovic currently serves as the Senior Vice President of Strategic Management at Intertek's North America Consumer Goods division. He previously worked at the Consumer Product Safety Commission from 2002 to 2006 and served in the New Mexico State Legislature from 1999 to 2002. Mohorovic has a B.A. from the University of Texas at Austin and an M.B.A. from the University of New Mexico.